## 🚀 Quick Start

### Example Workflow: Encrypt → Train → Verify

#### Step 1: Initialize Keys
```bash
# Generate Kyber encryption key
quantum-refiner keys generate-kyber --key-id dataset_key_1 --expires-days 365

# Generate Dilithium signing key
quantum-refiner keys generate-dilithium --key-id sign_key_1 --expires-days 365
```

#### Step 2: Encrypt Dataset
```bash
quantum-refiner dataset encrypt \
  /path/to/dataset.bin my_llm_dataset \
  --kyber-key dataset_key_1 \
  --dilithium-key sign_key_1
```

Output:
```
🔒 Encrypting dataset: dataset.bin
📦 Reading chunks...
🔐 Computing chunk hashes...
🌳 Building Merkle tree...
🔑 Performing Kyber encapsulation...
🔒 Encrypting chunks...
✍️  Signing manifest...
✅ Dataset encrypted successfully!
   Dataset ID: my_llm_dataset
   Chunks: 156
   Merkle Root: 3a7f2e...
```

#### Step 3: List Keys
```bash
quantum-refiner keys list-keys
```

#### Step 4: Verify Integrity
```bash
quantum-refiner verify dataset-integrity my_llm_dataset \
  --dilithium-public-key <public_key_hex>
```

#### Step 5: Decrypt for Training
```bash
quantum-refiner dataset decrypt \
  my_llm_dataset \
  /path/to/decrypted_data.bin \
  dataset_key_1 \
  --dilithium-public-key <public_key_hex>
```

#### Step 6: Secure Training
```bash
quantum-refiner train demo my_llm_dataset dataset_key_1 \
  --batch-size 32 \
  --epochs 1
```

